      "startNodeId": "N001_INTRO",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N001_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The Copy and Fax Room smells like hot plastic and old staples. The fax machine is idle in the way a machine looks idle when it\u2019s still warm.\n\nIn the tray: a curled, half-fed printout. Legal\u2019s Work Order, rendered in exhausted ink\u2014half text, half ghosts.",
          "next": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N010_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_PULL",
              "text": "use: Pull the pages from the tray.",
              "next": "N020_PULL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_RERUN_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Re-run the fax until the Work Order is legible (and make a duplicate).",
              "next": "N100_RERUN_START"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_HEADER",
              "text": "look: Check the header and routing line.",
              "next": "N030_HEADER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW_SERVICE_MODE",
              "text": "show: Use a service code sticker to adjust print density.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "item",
                  "itemId": "ITEM_SERVICE_CODE_STICKER",
                  "has": true
                },
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 10
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N200_SERVICE_MODE",
              "onFailNext": "N201_SERVICE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N900_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N020_PULL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The top page is a Work Order template\u2014half text, half afterimage.\n\nThe signature block is present. The scope paragraph is not.\n\nIt\u2019s enough to start an argument, not enough to end one.",
          "next": "N021_PULL_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N021_PULL_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_PULL_RERUN",
              "text": "use: Re-run the fax until it\u2019s legible.",
              "next": "N100_RERUN_START"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PULL_HEADER",
              "text": "look: Check the header and routing line again.",
              "next": "N030_HEADER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PULL_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PULL_LEAVE_BAD",
              "text": "leave: Keep the bad copy and move on.",
              "next": "N910_END_BAD_COPY"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N030_HEADER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The header line prints in blocky, exhausted characters:\n\nROUTE: OLEA LEGAL \u2014 OUTBOUND / DEST: FACILITY FAX (POSTED)\nREF: WO-RET-SP01\n\nThe timestamp is five minutes ago. The machine is still warm, like it wants credit.",
          "next": "N031_AFTER_HEADER_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N031_AFTER_HEADER_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_HEADER_RERUN",
              "text": "use: Re-run the fax until the Work Order is legible (and make a duplicate).",
              "next": "N100_RERUN_START"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_HEADER_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_HEADER_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N900_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N100_RERUN_START",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Run it again. Two clean sets.",
          "next": "N101_FIRST_RESULTS"
        },
        {
          "id": "N101_FIRST_RESULTS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The fax machine wakes up with a complaint disguised as a motor.\n\nPage one prints crisp at the top and dissolves in the middle.\nPage two prints the middle perfectly and sacrifices the asset line to a smear.",
          "next": "N110_RERUN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N110_RERUN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_RERUN_AGAIN",
              "text": "use: Re-run again.",
              "next": "N120_RERUN_AGAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RERUN_SERVICE_MODE",
              "text": "show: Use a service code sticker to adjust print density.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "item",
                  "itemId": "ITEM_SERVICE_CODE_STICKER",
                  "has": true
                },
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 10
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N200_SERVICE_MODE",
              "onFailNext": "N201_SERVICE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RERUN_PATCHWORK",
              "text": "look: Compare the best lines and assemble a \u201cmost legible\u201d set.",
              "next": "N140_PATCHWORK"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RERUN_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RERUN_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Stop here. It\u2019s \u201cgood enough.\u201d",
              "next": "N920_END_GOOD_ENOUGH"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N120_RERUN_AGAIN",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Again.",
          "next": "N121_AGAIN_RESULTS"
        },
        {
          "id": "N121_AGAIN_RESULTS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The machine tries a new failure mode\u2014this time the header line is perfect and the signature is a bruise.\n\nLegal\u2019s name is readable, but the pen stroke looks like it was done while bracing for impact.",
          "next": "N122_AGAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N122_AGAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_AGAIN_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Re-run until you have two fully legible sets.",
              "next": "N160_SUCCESS_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_AGAIN_PATCHWORK",
              "text": "look: Keep the cleanest lines and stop.",
              "next": "N140_PATCHWORK"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_AGAIN_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_AGAIN_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Give up for now.",
              "next": "N900_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N140_PATCHWORK",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lay the pages out, selecting sentences like you\u2019re building a body from acceptable parts.\n\nWhat you end up with reads like a fence built out of clauses:\n\n\u201cWORK ORDER \u2014 RETIREMENT SUPPORT (NARROW PURPOSE)\u201d\n\u201cASSET: SP-01 (as labeled on site)\u201d\n\u201cSCOPE: Closure-support activities limited to verification and documentation steps listed on the standard retirement checklist.\u201d\n\u201cEXCLUSIONS: No exploratory testing. No evaluation of anomalous conditions. No language implying \u2018authorization to enter.\u2019\u201d\n\u201cTHIS INSTRUMENT CONFIRMS TASK DESCRIPTION ONLY. It does not certify site condition, personnel training, or safety baseline.\u201d\n\nThe last line is underlined twice, like someone pressed too hard.",
          "next": "N141_PATCHWORK_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N141_PATCHWORK_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_PATCHWORK_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Re-run until you have two fully legible pages each.",
              "next": "N160_SUCCESS_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PATCHWORK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PATCHWORK_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Take the patched set and move on.",
              "next": "N930_END_PATCHWORK"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N200_SERVICE_MODE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Service mode. Darken.",
          "next": "N205_SERVICE_MODE_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N205_SERVICE_MODE_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The sticker peels reluctantly, like it was saving itself for an emergency that mattered.\n\nYou key in a code that should not be common knowledge. The machine accepts it without comment, which is its own kind of comment.\n\nThe next print is darker. The words stop trying to disappear.",
          "next": "N210_SERVICE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N210_SERVICE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_SERVICE_DUP",
              "text": "use: Print a duplicate set for the closure binder.",
              "next": "N160_SUCCESS_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SERVICE_READ",
              "text": "look: Read the scope language carefully.",
              "next": "N220_READ_SCOPE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SERVICE_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the tray options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SERVICE_LEAVE_ONE",
              "text": "leave: Stop after one set.",
              "next": "N940_END_ONE_SET"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N220_READ_SCOPE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The scope language is narrow enough to fit through a mail slot.\n\nEvery helpful noun is paired with an unhelpful disclaimer, like Legal is stapling you to the document at a safe distance.",
          "next": "N221_READ_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N221_READ_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_READ_DUP",
              "text": "use: Print a duplicate set for the closure binder.",
              "next": "N160_SUCCESS_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_READ_BACK_SERVICE",
              "text": "ask: Back.",
              "next": "N222_REDIRECT_SERVICE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_READ_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Pocket it and go.",
              "next": "N940_END_ONE_SET"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N222_REDIRECT_SERVICE",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N210_SERVICE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N201_SERVICE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You reach for the \u201cright numbers\u201d and come up short.\n\nEither you don\u2019t have the sticker, or you don\u2019t have the procedure down clean enough to risk it. The machine keeps its bland, default contrast\u2014perfect for receipts, terrible for liability.",
          "next": "N110_RERUN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N160_SUCCESS_PRINT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "On the next passes, the printer finally commits to the idea of ink.\n\nYou end up with two legible Work Order pages, duplicated, edges still warm. They agree with each other\u2014an institutional miracle.\n\nThe machine keeps its faint mechanical hum for a second longer than necessary, as if waiting for you to ask it to certify something.",
          "next": "N170_END_SUCCESS"
        },
        {
          "id": "N170_END_SUCCESS",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "receive_work_order_pages",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "paperwork.workOrderReceived",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "inventory.items",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "ITEM_WORK_ORDER_LEGAL"
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.completeness",
              "action": "increment",
              "value": 2
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N900_END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N910_END_BAD_COPY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Better than nothing.",
          "next": "N911_END_BAD_COPY"
        },
        {
          "id": "N911_END_BAD_COPY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You fold the pages anyway. The fold goes through the only readable sentence.",
          "next": "N912_END_BAD_COPY"
        },
        {
          "id": "N912_END_BAD_COPY",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N920_END_GOOD_ENOUGH",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You can already hear an auditor saying \u201cgood enough\u201d like it\u2019s profanity.",
          "next": "N921_END_GOOD_ENOUGH"
        },
        {
          "id": "N921_END_GOOD_ENOUGH",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N930_END_PATCHWORK",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You keep the best of the damage. The binder will have to forgive you.",
          "next": "N931_END_PATCHWORK"
        },
        {
          "id": "N931_END_PATCHWORK",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N940_END_ONE_SET",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You fold it carefully, avoiding the clean paragraph like it\u2019s a wound. One set isn\u2019t a binder. It\u2019s a promise you haven\u2019t backed up yet.",
          "next": "N941_END_ONE_SET"
        },
        {
          "id": "N941_END_ONE_SET",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
